effectiveValue.description: Output only. The effective value of the setting at the given parent resource, evaluated based on the resource hierarchy The effective value evaluates to one of the following options, in this order. If an option is not valid or doesn't exist, then the next option is used: 1. The local setting value on the given resource: Setting.local_value 2. If one of the given resource's ancestors in the resource hierarchy have a local setting value, the local value at the nearest such ancestor. 3. The setting's default value: SettingMetadata.default_value 4. An empty value, defined as a `Value` with all fields unset. The data type of Value must always be consistent with the data type defined in Setting.metadata.
